  "generated_text": "To find the percentage of students enrolled in hip-hop dance, we can break down the problem step-by-step:\n\n1.  **Total number of students**: 20\n2.  **Contemporary dance enrollment**: $20\\%$ of 20.\n    $$0.20 \\times 20 = 4 \\text{ students}$$\n3.  **Remaining students after contemporary dance**:\n    $$20 - 4 = 16 \\text{ students}$$\n4.  **Jazz dance enrollment**: $25\\%$ of the remaining 16 students.\n    $$0.25 \\times 16 = 4 \\text{ students}$$\n5.  **Remaining students after jazz dance (Hip-hop)**:\n    $$16 - 4 = 12 \\text{ students}$$\n\nAlternatively, we can calculate the percentage directly without finding the exact number first:\n*   Students in Contemporary: $20\\%$\n*   Remaining after Contemporary: $100\\% - 20\\% = 80\\%$\n*   Students in Jazz: $25\\%$ of the remaining $80\\%$\n    $$0.25 \\times 80\\% = 20\\%$$\n*   Remaining students after Jazz (Hip-hop):\n    $$100\\% - 20\\% = 80\\%$$\n\nSo, 80% of the students enrolled in hip-hop dance.\n\n\\boxed{80\\%}\n",
